chargeHist.descr: Battery to a Law Enforcement Officer

result.execSummary:
The defendant Kimberly J. Stockwell was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Attempt Battery to a Law Enforcement Officer, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.203(2).
  • Possession of Methamphetamine, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Cases called at 8:59 AM: 20CT326, 21CT1062, 21CF1218, 21CF1357, 21CM144, 22CF123, 22CF321, 22CM151.
Defendant Kimberly J. Stockwell in custody and in court with Attorney Robert Allen Thorson.   Attorney Matthew Kirkpatrick in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Agreement has been reached. Victim/Witness statute complied with. Defendant is advised of charges, maximum penalties, elements of the crime(s) and constitutional rights. 
20CF123: Defendant pleads No Contest to Count 1: Felony Bail Jumping.
22CF321: Defendant pleads No Contest to Count 1: Battery To Law Enforcement Officer; Attempt and Count 2: Possession of Methamphetamine.
Court accepts the pleas and finds the Defendant guilty. Counsel makes statements regarding the plea agreement.
Sentence is Withheld and the Defendant is placed on 3 Years of Probation with the following conditions:
60 Days of Jail (Huber eligibility to be determined at a later date) stayed pending further order of the Court (22CF123). 
No contact with Detective Ryan Lambeseder except in his official capacity as a law enforcement officer. 
Write a letter of apology to Detective Lambeseder within 30 days; letter is to be given to the agent who will provide a copy to the State.
No contact with K.H. or  M.L. No contact with any known drug dealers/users except in a therapeutic setting. Contact with her adult children only if approved in writing by the agent ahead of time.
AODA and follow through with recommendations. Maintain absolute sobriety. 
Defendant not to consume/possess any alcohol or go into any taverns, bars, liquor stores/place where alcohol is primarily served/sold. 
Defendant not to consume/use/possess any illegal drugs/non-prescribed medications/controlled substances or drug paraphernalia. 
Any conditions, programming or treatment per the agent and follow through with recommendations. 
Defendant is granted 69 days of sentence credit in 22CF321 and 22CF123. Remaining charges are dismissed and read in.
Status conference on May 20, 2022 at 09:00 am.

(Cases 20CT326, 21CF1062, 21CF1218, 21CF1357, 21CM144, 22CF123, 22CF321, 22CM151 are called at 9:48 AM) Defendant Kimberly J. Stockwell in court, in custody.  Attorney Robert Allen Thorson in court for Kimberly J. Stockwell. Deputy District Attorney Angela Beranek appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 
22CF123- Defendant waives right to a preliminary hearing and Court accepts waiver. 
22CF123 and 22CF321- Defense acknowledges receipt of Information in 22CF321 and acknowledges the Information in 22CF123 will mirror the criminal complaint, waives reading, enters Not Guilty pleas to all counts. Court receives Not Guilty pleas. 
Status Conference in 20CT326, 21CF1062, 21CF1218, 21CF1357, 21CM144, 22CF123, 22CF321, 22CM151: 05/20/2022 at 9:00 AM.
Return on warrant on May 17, 2022 at 09:45 am.

(11:21 AM cases 22CM151, 22CF123, 22CF321 called.) Prosecuting attorney Afton Lewis in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Kimberly J. Stockwell appeared by video, in custody in the Eau Claire County Jail. Attorney Robert Allen Thorson appeared by video for Kimberly J. Stockwell.
Attorney Thorson requests the bond be amended to a lower cash bond around the amount of $500.00. State opposes any bond modification.
Court enters Not Guilty pleas on the defendant's behalf to all counts in all cases and refers all cases to be heard in Branch 1, presumably the branch with the oldest felony file.
Court orders bond modification request is denied at this time and may be heard in the assigned branch.

(Cases 22CF321, 22CM151 are called at 2:30 PM) Defendant Kimberly J. Stockwell in court, in custody.  Attorney Robert Allen Thorson in court for Kimberly J. Stockwell.  Attorney Andrew James Gunderson in court for State of Wisconsin. 
22CF321- State calls Detective Mitchell Hunsley, Eau Claire Police Department- sworn and testifies. Cross-examination of Detective Hunsley by Defense. Witness excused. 
Court finds probable cause and binds the matter over. Arraignment to be scheduled with Branch 2 Judicial Assistant.
